JOHANNESBURG - Labour Minister Mildred Oliphant is awaiting a report from Cosatu on the disrupted Workers Day event.Oliphant says workers would not have booed President Zuma if they understood that working conditions had improved under his leadership. Oliphant says ANC members should stop calling for President Zuma's head and support the party's constitution instead. Oliphant says South African workers rights have improved considerably. eNCA